<paragraph blockId="23.[264,1324,284,1070]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName box="[437,760,884,909]" class="Entognatha" family="Arrhopalitidae" genus="Arrhopalites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="botuveraensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[437,760,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Arrhopalites botuveraensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[774,843,884,910]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(South 
<collectingCountry box="[948,1021,884,910]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) belongs to the coecusgroup, it is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[528,662,924,949]" class="Entognatha" family="Arrhopalitidae" genus="Arrhopalites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amorimi">
<emphasis box="[528,662,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A. amorimi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Southeast 
<collectingCountry box="[806,879,924,950]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[948,1104,924,949]" class="Entognatha" family="Arrhopalitidae" genus="Arrhopalites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vazquezae">
<emphasis box="[948,1104,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A. vazquezae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1122,1217,924,950]" name="Mexico" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Mexico</collectingCountry>
), despite the disconnected distribution. The new species can be distinguished by the absence of tunica in the first unguis and the indistinctly ringed 
<number box="[914,928,1004,1030]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="5.0">5</number>
subsegments of fourth antennal segment.
</paragraph>
